{
  "texts": [
    "M4To find out the limitation of Named Entity recognition approaches from existing research articles.Step II: Related workResearch articles from the years 2010 to 2023 are selected in this step based on the RQs.",
    "According to their titles, abstracts, and keywords related to Named entity recognition, the papers are included.To find the related works, we followed the following subsections:(a) In order to find research papers on Named entity recognition, the following search engines are used: ACM digitallibrary (https://dl.acm.org/),  Elsevier (https://www.elsevier.com/en-in/),  Google Scholar (https://scholar.google.com/),  IEEE Xplore (https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/Xplore/home.jsp),  ScienceDirect (https://www.sciencedirect.com/),  Springer (https://www.springer.com/in),  Web of Science (https://clarivate.com/webofsciencegroup/solutions/web-ofscience/) (b) The following keywords were used to identify the papers: (Natural Language Processing (NLP) OR text OR Named entity recognition (NER) OR Part of speech (POS) OR word OR document OR information retrieval (IR) OR question answering OR sentiment analysis (SA) OR text summarization (TS) anywhere in the paper.",
    "(c) The papers from journals, transactions, and conference proceedings have also been manually reviewed based on their titles.",
    "The research papers on Named entity recognition that have been chosen are quite relevant.",
    "The method used to choose the research papers for the literature review is depicted in Figure 2."
  ]
}